                  <additions>
                     <lb/>
                     <label>Inscriptions:</label>
                     <list><item>Folio <locus from ="1a" to="1a">1a</locus> bears an Arabic supplicatory prayer derived from prophetic traditions:<lb/>
                     <q xml:lang="ar">اللهم زین ظواهرنا بخدمتک و بواطننا بمعرفتک و قلوبنا بمحبتک و
                        ارواحنا بمعاونتک و اسرارنا بمشاهدتک اللهم اجعل فی
                        قلبی نورا و فی سمعی نورا و فی بصری نورا و فی مخی نورا و عن
                        یمینی نورا و عن شمالی نورا
                        و عن فوقی نورا و تحتی نورا برحمتک یا ارحم الراحمین</q>
                     </item>
                        <item>Folio <locus from ="104b" to="104b">104b</locus> bears a Persian inscription, presumaby by a non-native, roughly translates as:
                           <q xml:lang="en">This book was
                           bought from the nation of Greek at the most prosperous
                           time of Constantinople and around Petersburg, was written
                           in the year of 8571 [NB: probably <date cert="high" calendar="#Gregorian" when="1758"
                              >1758</date>] of Gregorian calendar</q>, with another note beneath in English:
                           <q xml:lang="en">M.S. Pers.</q>
                           </item>
                        
                     </list>
